> Joe Martin wrote:
> >
> > National Semiconductor make an "LM317" 3 terminal adjustable
> regulator which
> > can easily be used as a current limiter. I am not sure if the
> schematic for
> > this particular application is included with the Data sheets so
> I'll add it
> > here.
> >
> > Current Limiter
> >
> > ________________     R1
> > Vin       |LM317|___/\/\/\_________Iout
> >           |_____|Vout     |
> >              |            |
> >          Vadj|____________|
> >
> > Iout = 1.25/R1 where I is the output amperage
> >
> > Joe Martin
